<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2001</DATELINE><TITLE>Epidemiology and prevention of pediatric viral respiratory infections in health-care institutions.</TITLE><BODY>Nosocomial viral respiratory infections cause considerable illness and death on pediatric wards. Common causes of these infections include respiratory syncytial virus and influenza. Although primarily a community pathogen, rhinovirus also occasionally results in hospitalization and serious sequelae. This article reviews effective infection control interventions for these three pathogens, as well as ongoing controversies.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>